http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/80-hurt-in-kite-flying-accidents/article14000586.ece

Amid celebrations on the first day of Makar Sankranti, at least 80 people, mostly children, were on Thursday injured in kite-flying related accidents in Jaipur city, officials said.Thirteen injured persons, including two women, were admitted to various wards including orthopaedic in the hospital and the rest were discharged after first aid, SMS Trauma Hospital Deputy Superintendent Jagdish Modi told PTI. Thirty-one persons sustained injures after being entangled in kite strings while riding their vehicles, Dr. Modi said.-PTI